4:Tb68,<h2>How to Get Your Florida Driver's License</h2>
<p>You have 30 days after establishing Florida residency to get your Florida driver's license. Here's exactly how to do it.</p>
<h2>What You Need</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Proof of identity</strong> — US passport, birth certificate, or valid out-of-state license</li>
<li><strong>Proof of Social Security number</strong> — SS card, W-2, or 1099</li>
<li><strong>Two proofs of Florida residency</strong> — Utility bill, bank statement, lease agreement, or mortgage docs</li>
<li><strong>Payment</strong> — $48 for a Class E license (most common)</li>
</ul>
<h2>Step-by-Step Process</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong>Gather your documents</strong> — See the list above. Bring originals, not copies.</li>
<li><strong>Visit a Florida DHSMV office</strong> — Find your nearest location at <a href="https://www.flhsmv.gov/offices/">flhsmv.gov</a></li>
<li><strong>Complete the application</strong> — Available online or at the office</li>
<li><strong>Pass the vision test</strong> — Basic eye exam done on-site</li>
<li><strong>Pass the written test</strong> — 50 questions, need 40 correct (80%). Waived if you surrender a valid out-of-state license.</li>
<li><strong>Get your photo taken</strong> — Your temporary license prints on the spot</li>
<li><strong>Receive your permanent license</strong> — Mailed to your Florida address within 7–10 business days</li>
</ol>
<h2>Tips</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Go early</strong> — DHSMV offices get packed after 10am</li>
<li><strong>Book online if available</strong> — Some locations offer appointments</li>
<li><strong>Surrender your old license</strong> — Florida requires you to give up your out-of-state license</li>
<li><strong>Update your registration too</strong> — You have 10 days to register your vehicle in Florida</li>
</ul>
<h2>Fees</h2>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Service</th>
<th>Cost</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Class E License (standard)</td>
<td>$48</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Real ID upgrade</td>
<td>No extra cost</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Motorcycle endorsement</td>
<td>$48</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>CDL</td>
<td>$75</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h2>FAQs</h2>
<h3>Do I need to take a driving test?</h3>
<p>No — if you have a valid out-of-state license, the road test is waived. You'll still need to pass the vision test.</p>
<h3>Can I keep my out-of-state license?</h3>
<p>No. Florida law requires you to surrender your previous license when you get a Florida one.</p>
<h3>What if my out-of-state license is expired?</h3>
<p>If it's been expired for more than a year, you'll need to take both the written and road tests.</p>
<hr>
<p>Just moved to Tampa Bay? <a href="https://nowtb.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="affiliate-link">The NOW Team — Barrett Henry, REALTOR®</a> can help you get settled in your new home while you check off the rest of your moving checklist.</p>
